<br>
So, after procrastinating for far too long, it's time to proceed with my epic quest.  There are two parts I'm concerning myself with right now, item hunts, and the first set of battles.<br>
<br>
With my current difficulties in gathering people, I've decided to see if there's general interest, and finish off a few of them in one fell swoop.  There are six total, my hope is to gather people and do two or three in a day, given that they're single mobs, triggered, and don't require a huge area to be cleared, I think that's not unreasonable.  But time will tell.<br>
<br>
The mobs are level 55, and hit for 225 max, and may flurry.  They're unslowable, and most have procs, good MR is a must for some.  Which ones we'll attempt depends on the relative strength of the force assembled.  As far as I've heard, fire is the best spell type to use.<br>
<br>
From the more difficult ones, to the easiest:<br>
Swamp of No Hope<br>
fight takes place underwater.  clerics and melees need EB.    nukers can only land spells from above the water.  spirits procs a &quot;whirl till you hurl&quot; type spell.<br>
<br>
Permafrost<br>
fight takes place in the bear pits, these need to be cleared beforehand and the fight should be over before respawn.  spirit hits fast.  Defensive warrior might be required for this one. procs 400dd.  lots of HP.<br>
<br>
LFay<br>
procs a blind, hit fairly fast.<br>
<br>
EJ<br>
casts aoe fear.<br>
<br>
Feerott<br>
procs aoe dot/snare, 9 counters, 100hp per tick<br>
<br>
Stonebrunt<br>
wisp, high AC.  procs dispel/stun.<br>
<br>
Scout Locations: <br>
<br>
1) Permafrost - Scout Janomin (by Entrance/ladder, behind some rocks)<br>
2) Lesser Faydark - Scout Rahjiq (187, -1885)<br>
3) Feerrott - Scout Ahlikal (374, -2439)<br>
4) Swamp of No Hope. - Scout Eyru (-3614, 2345)<br>
5) Stonebrunt Mountains - Scout Malom (3650, -3530)<br>
6) Emerald Jungle - Scout Vyrak (237, 4212)<br>
<br>
